        "title": "What does `I/System.out: -1` mean in Android?",
        "body": "<p>I have created programmatically a <code>RelativeLayout<\/code> which contains a <code>textView<\/code>. I'm trying to get the id of the <code>textView<\/code> using this code:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(textView.getId());\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>When i try to see the result it prints out -1? What does it mean?\nThanks!<\/p>\n",
